ATLANTA CITY COUNCIL NATIVE HOME OWNER RESIDENCE RESOLUTION

WHEREAS, an essential duty of government is the protection, welfare, and security of all its citizens;

WHEREAS, native, legacy, and generational Atlanta residence whom have purchased and lived in their homes for any duration should not fear losing their home due to an exponential property tax increase;

WHEREAS, an important part of the culture and historical value of Atlanta is drawn from it’s native population; and if that population is removed, then the cultural and historical value will also diminish.

AND WHEREAS, equally essential to ensuring the welfare and security of our citizens is a fair and effective system which safeguards the civil liberties and presumption of the right to own and keep property while also recognizing that the sudden and repeated exponential rises in the percentages of property taxes pose a threat to native home owners who become victims of a government entity which enacts such burdens.

WHEREAS, open and efficient communications among all participants in the private and governmental system - elected officials, government administrators and the public – will strengthen the system and provide more transparency about how the percentage rates are decided upon and give the public a voice in the decision making process.

WHEREAS, a proper and more equitable outcome to such unchecked increases in property taxes would be a set percentage cap of no more than 1.5% in any given year.  

WHEREAS, the over taxation of the people’s goods and services, labor, capitol gains, inheritance, licensing, fees, and other forms of collection by the government, both State and Federal; has already burdened the citizenry, who then can lose their home and livelyhood in any given year by a single property tax hike.

THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Atlanta City Council recommends that the State Legislature of Georgia enact into Law a maximum 1.5% property tax cap for increases made in any given year in order to preserve the legacy and heritage of our Atlanta and Georgia Native Constituents.
